culated?</span><hr size=1> Say you had a 15/30 weapon with <br>
<br>
a) Bane DMG: X+5 ... If the creature you are fighting is type X, weapon is 20/30, if not... 15/30<br>
<br>
b) Cold/Fire/Magic/Poison/Disease DMG: 5 ... On each sucessfull hit, if the creature fails its resistist, weapon is 20/30, if they do not fail the resists (or are immune to that type of damage)... 15/30<br>
<br>
Illandra Azuyrne<br>
Level 58 Paladin - Xegony <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#666666><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/uaalnydara.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Aalnydara</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FFFFFF>(12/13/01 1:29:02 am)</font><br>    <BR><img src=http://scf.usc.edu/~rbolger/eq/ally_ezboard_pic.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: How is the new damage calculated?</span><hr size=1> Just curious...where did you come up with that?  I'm not denying it's true.  I'm just wondering where you got the information from because it's seems like you just pulled it out of thin air.<br>
