Level 58 Paladin - Xegony <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#666666><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/ubending.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Bending</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FFFFFF>(12/13/01 7:50:45 am)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: How is the new damage calculated?</span><hr size=1> Still a bit cunfused. My Soulfire has a DMG Bonus of 17 and stats are 23/45 (so it says when I click on it).<br>
Do I hit with 100 instead of 83 because of the Bonus, or do I have a 40/45 weapon?<br>
And..that DMG Bonus has nothing to do with the Level DMG Bonus right? <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#666666><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/uillandraazuryne.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Illandra Azuryne</A>&nbsp; <IMG SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/image/globalBlack.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FFFFFF>(12/13/01 8:01:30 am)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: How is the new damage calculated?</span><hr size=1> &quot;Do I hit with 100 instead of 83 because of the Bonus&quot;<br>
<br>
Yes<br>
<br>
&quot;My Soulfire has a DMG Bonus of 17 and stats are 23/45 &quot;<br>
<br>
So the minimum you should ever hit with this weapon is 18 (1 + 17)<br>
<br>
The number you will find yourself hitting more than any other number (the mode or Magic Number) is<br>
<br>
(2*23)+17 = 63<br>
<br>
The Max Damage you will hit for will be <br>
<br>
((Your Strength + You 2H weapon Skill)/100)*23 + 17<br>
<br>
You will have to calculate that one yourself <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br>
<br>
Illandra Azuryne<br>
